<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted by the All Party Parliamentary Group on Population, Development and Reproductive Health, and Marie Stopes International</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">All Party Parliamentary Group on Population, Development and Reproductive Health, and Marie </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Stopes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> International</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The All Party Parliamentary Group </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(APPG) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">on Population, Development and Reproductive Health </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">supports initiatives that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> increase access to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and improve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ments in, reproductive and sexual health </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">worldwide. The group </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">currently </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">has over 70 members, from the House of Commons and the House of Lords, representing the UK's main political parties.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In July 2013 the APPG organised a study tour </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to Myanmar.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The delegation comprised Meg Munn MP, John Mann MP, Heather Wheeler MP, Craig Whittaker MP and Baroness </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Jenkin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tour aimed to increase understanding of the MPs’ knowledge and expertise in sexual and reproductive health and rights (SRHR) and to increase </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">APPG </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">membership.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Marie </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Stopes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> International (MSI) is one of the world’s largest family planning and reproductive health organisations. MSI delivers quality services to poor and underserved women in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">37</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> countries, focusing on services that deliver impact, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">quality, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">choice</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> equity. MSI is one of the few providers of reproductive health services in Myanmar. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Despite the challenges</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">since </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">MSI </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">were established in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">1998 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">they </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">have provided </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">integrated sexual and reproductive healthcare services to hundreds </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">thousands of people. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ervices include family planning, HIV/STI testing and treatment, maternal health serv</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ices and post abortion care</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">MSI’s focus is on reaching underserved and marginalised women in remote, rural communities working in partnership with the Ministry of Health to help strengthen local health systems.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">MSI services currently</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> reach around 15% of the population through outreach</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> teams</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, 25 centres and through community based health workers and social marketing. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Myanmar’s health indicators are among</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">st</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the worst in the Asia Pacific region. One woman dies for every 260</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">babies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> born and only one in three women use any modern method of contraception. The leading cause of death and disability for women is pregnancy and child birth. Less than two per cent of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">current </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">GDP is spent on healthcare. An under-funded and under resourced public health system means that services delivered by non-government organisations are essential to create access to even basic healthcare.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Other challenges to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> delivering </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">health </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">services include:</span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Deep inequality </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and poverty</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Low resourcing of health sector </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">leads to limited access and poor quality </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">resulting</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in low utilisation of facilities</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Two thirds of the population live in remote areas </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Conflict and displacement</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Young population - unmarried young women face particular challenges in accessing services</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Restricted and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> pro-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">natalist</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> political climate - </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">or example abortion is highly restricted and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> as a result the rate of death </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">and disability </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">caused by unsafe abortion is particularly </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">high.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">R</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ecent announcements </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">from the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Ministry of Health </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">have been</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> positive</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. F</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">or example </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a commitment to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> quadruple the health budget</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">pledge</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">made in November 2013 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">under the FP2020 initiative. However SRHR remain</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> sensitive in Myanmar</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s a result service providers face numerous political challenges and restrictions. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Quality r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">eproductive health </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">services are critical to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">alleviating </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">poverty</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and achieving</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> gender equity</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. DFID’s current health programmes in Myanmar </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">deliver </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">strong </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">returns on investment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">have made </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tangible difference </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">both saving lives and improving wider development outcomes. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">DFID support has enabled the MSI programme to substantially expand access </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">over the last few years </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">particularly through outreach services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to reach rural areas</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n 2012 MSI in Burma served 300,329 clients and saved the health system over £3 million pounds.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This programme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> is featured in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">short film that can be viewed here: </span><a href="http://www.mariestopes.org/news/midwives-myanmar"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.mariestopes.org/news/midwives-myanmar</span></a></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">DFID have been a key agency in mobilising health dono</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in Myanmar</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and play a vital role in supporting the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">health sector</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">DFID are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">well placed to co-ordinate </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and influence </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">other donors</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">continue to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">strengthen the health sector through provision of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">funding, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">technical assistance, developing joint initiatives and supporting </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">development of a financed and equitable</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> longer term </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">health strategy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. We would support the recent recommendations made by the Independent Commission for Aid </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">evaluation into health programmes in Burma</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> For example</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> recommendation one stating</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">‘DFID should leverage its relationship with the Ministry of Health and its experience in Burma to date to focus the in-flows of health aid and accelerate the building of a more robust health system, including better integration of the for-profit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">sector.’</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Given</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> DFID’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> success’ to date, reputation in this area</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">potential </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">opportunities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for future success</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> we would encourage DFID to continue its leadership and commitment to health</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (including reproductive health)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and to scale up resources to this sector.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><a name="_GoBack"></a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What role can DFID play in strengthening the health system?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">To support the Ministry of Health to develop a longer term vision for the health system </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to develop</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> innovative </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">mechanisms</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and partnerships </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to finance it. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">To encourage</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the government to work in partnership with providers such as MSI to fill gaps, scale up services and harness potential of private providers. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">To encourage the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">government to train and build the capacity of rural health workers particularly midwives, and to empower them to provide services in isolated rural areas. </span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What should DFID be doing more of?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Continue to prioritise investment in health - prioritising sexual and reproductive health services which offer the most cost effective way to improve health and development indicators. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Prioritise delivery and access to primary health care services in rural areas and for excluded communities.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Continuing to work with other donors to ensure co-ordination and pooling of resources.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Provision of technical assistance - particularly on health financing, infrastructure investments (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">eg</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for supplies and commodities) and training health workers at scale.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">January 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/228499/ICAI-Burma-health-management-response-aug13.pdf"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/228499/ICAI-Burma-health-management-response-aug13.pdf</span></a></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:4pt 0pt"><span style="color:#4c4c4c; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></body></html>